    "description": "The OGC API - Processes standard supports the wrapping of computational tasks into executable processes that can be offered by a server through a Web API and be invoked by a client application. It specifies a processing interface for communicating over a RESTful protocol using JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) encodings. The standard builds on concepts from the OGC Web Processing Service (WPS) 2.0 Interface Standard but provides a more modern approach, allowing for interaction with web resources using the OpenAPI specification. Importantly, it does not require implementation of a WPS interface.",
